history.content: I know phase 1 isn't for another few months, but I'm starting to think about the classes I will be taking for fall 2018, which will be my last semester before graduating. I saw the draft schedule (https://www2.eecs.berkeley.edu/Scheduling/CS/schedule-draft.html) and definitely want to take 162 and 168. Technically I don't need another upper div to graduate, but I feel like I would rather take another tech than take a class that I'm not really interested in. I was thinking of adding on 160 to this schedule, but I've heard the class can be heavy workload project-wise and can conflict with 162 in that sense. I couldn't find any questions about this specific schedule on piazza so I figured I'd ask. Does 160 (currently set to be with paulos), 162, and 168 sound doable if I don't have a lot of extracurricular commitment? If not, which upper div cs class (or interesting tech elective) would be good to do with this schedule? I've already taken c100, 161, 170, 186, and 188.
history.subject: Course advice fall 2018
